New Year, Same Me, New Mom! 🤰✨

Sending the best wishes and blessings your way in 2023🙏✨ We’re excited and humbled to share we will welcome our baby into the world and into our growing family in early June ♥️ Ahh!!!

I can’t get enough of celebrating this guy 🥳
 #38 #capricornseason #latergram

🎀 🧢  TBT finding out our baby’s sex on Christmas morning over @zoom with family. 

You can tell by our reaction it was 100% NOT what we were expecting..

We’re so excited!!!

30 weeks have gone by fast! We’re so close to meeting our baby 💙 

Thanks to Jules & Andi for bringing all my favorite Chicago girls together to celebrate!

From celebrating a new life one day to mourning a precious life of 87 years the next. I lost my grandma Mary on the evening of April 2, Palm Sunday. 

She was a faithful servant of God and someone who always encouraged me to trust in the Lord.

My heart is broken but I know my Grandma’s sweet soul is finally resting easy in the Kingdom of Heaven. I can’t wait to tell my son about our guardian angel.
This California-themed baby shower in ATL was so special and really felt like a page turner… 😭 the next time I see my girls, I’ll be a mom.

9 months after tying the knot and we’re hanging out in our nursery waiting on a new addition (🤯 !)

I want to bottle up this time as newlyweds, it has been my favorite, but I’m also so ready to meet our baby! #honeymoonbaby #nursery #babycomingsoon
Appreciation post for my first baby 🐶💕🥹 My baby girl! ILYSM! #paytonhester #loml
Hot dad walk with our baby boy 🔥 IYKYK. Happy Fathers Day @doctor.ben_ ! 🩵 The GOAT, we love you!
Over the moon you’ll find me 🌙
💔Rest in paradise sweet friend, with your angel pup by your side. We will never forget you. #fuckcancer

When you’re dividing and conquering with a newborn and a sick dog in the middle of the night 💁🏼‍♀️💁🏼‍♀️💁🏼‍♀️

You’re still the 🐐 @doctor.ben_ 😚

Looking back at my tiny baby Dax as I prepare to head back into the world next week. We have both grown so much in these months spent together. Turning pages and entering new chapters suddenly seems overwhelming and all too fast. 

Though I’m willing time to stop, I know we can do it. I’m going to make you proud champ!

10 years old today 💖 Took her out to the beach this morning to celebrate. Her run is a little sideways these days but she enjoys life just as much as she did when she was a puppy. P, I wish I could keep rewinding time and keep you forever. I love you girl 🐾

The holiday season is more magical than ever this year 🥹✨ 

Also my hand holding Santa’s and on his thigh 😂

From our family to yours, have an amazing holiday season —whatever season you’re in. 

So thankful for my love and our healthy happy kiddos this year! It was only a few years ago I was still dreaming about having a family of my own to celebrate Christmas with and I was starting to feel like it might not happen (circa 2020 I think you know what I’m talking about 😝). It wasn’t always easy around the holidays to watch it all unfold for seemingly everyone else in my life. I didn’t know how God would work in my life to make this dream come true but I’m feeling so much gratitude that I stayed in the game and remained hopeful. If you’re where I was, hang in there and enjoy the ride. Whatever you’re wishing for this year, sending prayers and peace your way. 

Let the fun begin 🎄💕🤶🎅 Merry Christmas and happy holidays to all!
